With my modest loans to Kiva Entrepreneurs -- especially group loans, I am part of  something very special -- supporting the Luctor et Emergo process of teams/people around the world.  This is very meaningful to me.

Thanks to the Kiva team for making this opportunity to participate, globally with local impact, available to me.
lenders.occupational_info:
By day, am an Organizational Development Consultant helping teams in healthcare, engineering and other professional service environments become more effective and efficient.

By night, am the Lead Co-Organizer of the Edmonton TheatreGoers Club.  We have alot of silly fun together at live theatre, music and other cultural events.  Check out our Club site:  http://www.meetup.com/EdmontonTheatreGoers/

lenders.occupational_info: My wife and I raise Angora goats and sell their mohair fiber, yarn and knit items.  I use a lathe and turn wooden tools for fiber artists such as drop spindles and things to wrap yarn on.  In addition I turn wooden bowls and plates for functional and decorative use.

lenders.occupational_info: I am an entrepreneur who started in his garage, much like you.  I have built a company that sells products in more than 5,000 retail stores around the world.  I hope you will do the same!
